          <p corresp='TTP1575437P0' xml:id='OTP1575437P0'>To his Excellency <rs ref='#S63111'>John J Pettus</rs> Governor of Mississippi.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1575437P1' xml:id='OTP1575437P1'>We the undersigned represent to your honour that a foul <rs ref='#S63926'>murder</rs> has been committed in this place by a man named <rs ref='#S74055'>Isaac N. Sample</rs> upon the person of <rs ref='#S74056'>Jerry Ryan</rs> on the 1<add place='above'>st</add> March 1861 and that the said Sample has <rs ref='#S63177'>fled from Justice</rs> and it is the impression of the undersigned that a reward should be offered by your excellency to have the said murderer brought to justice the said Sample is about 38 years of age weighs about 240 pounds light complexion and is very fond of drinking and a very profane man
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1575437P2' xml:id='OTP1575437P2'><hi rend='underline'><rs ref='#S74057'>Sulphur Springs Madison County</rs> Miss March 6<add place='above'>th</add> 1861</hi>
</p>

